      m_Calls: []
  m_text: "Projectile motion is a free-falling motion where an object, usually referred
    to as a projectile, flies over the air at a certain angle. The object\u2019s
    path is known as its trajectory. As it flies in the air, the velocity it gains
    has both horizontal and vertical components. This, along with the angle the ballistic
    is being thrown at, creates a parabolic trajectory."
  m_isRightToLeft: 0
  m_fontAsset: {fileID: 11400000, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
  m_sharedMaterial: {fileID: -4890204404628985631, guid: ed9fe41215e4a2c4a9fa581443855244, type: 2}
